 :tx/rationale "UNSOUNDNESS-LEDGER-4: Lattice resolution falls back to LWW silently. resolution.rs line ~158: ResolutionMode::Lattice { lattice_id } is declared in the schema but the lattice join is never computed — the code does '// Stage 0: fall back to LWW'. No warning is emitted. No datom records the fallback. No test verifies that lattice mode produces correct results (because it cannot — it produces LWW results). The Kani proof prove_lattice_join_associativity exists but proves the trivial LWW fallback, not a real lattice join — it is vacuously true. A user who configures ResolutionMode::Lattice for an attribute gets LWW without knowing it. Two agents making semantically-different assertions get the temporally-latest value, not the lattice lub. The schema is lying about the semantics it provides. The minimum fix is a warning datom when lattice mode is requested but not available, or a resolution receipt that records which mode was actually used vs which mode was configured."
